    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-10-23T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-10-23T10:00:00-05:00" n="473"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d473">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">822.00 Revolutions/85: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Guayaquil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">McDonough</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guayaquil</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-10-23T10:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 23, 1937—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 1:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The following telegram has been sent to the Legation at Quito: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>October 23, 9 a.m. Military authorities inform me that <hi rend="italic"
                                >coup d’état</hi> by General Enriquez is accepted by local garrison.
                            All is quiet <pb facs="0479" n="469" xml:id="pg_469"/> here, there have
                            been no disorders. Military authorities headquarters further inform me
                            that Colonel Icaza<note n="3" xml:id="d473fn3">Col. Pedro Icaza,
                                Commandant of the Guayaquil Military Zone.</note> is to be Minister
                            of National Defense and Victor Emilio Estrada will probably be Minister
                            of Hacienda”.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">McDonough</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
